
⚙️ Step-by-Step: Create VPC Peering
🟢 Step 1: Create Two VPCs

Example:

VPC-A → 10.0.0.0/16
VPC-B → 192.168.0.0/16

⚠️ Important:
👉 CIDR blocks must NOT overlap

🟢 Step 2: Create Peering Connection
Go to AWS Console → VPC
Click → Peering Connections
Click → Create Peering

Fill details:

Requester VPC → VPC-A
Accepter VPC → VPC-B
🟢 Step 3: Accept Peering
Go to Peering → Accept request
🟢 Step 4: Update Route Tables (MOST IMPORTANT 🔥)
In VPC-A Route Table:
Destination: 192.168.0.0/16
Target: VPC Peering Connection
In VPC-B Route Table:
Destination: 10.0.0.0/16
Target: VPC Peering Connection

👉 Without this → ❌ Communication will NOT work

🟢 Step 5: Update Security Groups

Allow traffic:

From other VPC CIDR
Example:
Type: All traffic
Source: 192.168.0.0/16
